01:13.013 --> 01:14.844
All right, let's get these shovels
moving here.

01:14.915 --> 01:15.711
Eh, where are we?

01:15.782 --> 01:16.578
The Con Club.

01:16.650 --> 01:18.140
Conservative Club?
/Yeah.

01:18.218 --> 01:20.049
We're not nicking their fucking
turf, are we?

01:20.120 --> 01:21.417
You're not a Tory, are you?
/No.

01:21.488 --> 01:23.285
Well what are you worried
about then?

01:23.357 --> 01:25.518
Yeah, the caretaker lives miles
away, there's no problem...

01:25.592 --> 01:27.856
all you've got to do...
is heads down... arses up...

01:27.928 --> 01:30.192
let's get into gear and make
a couple of bob, come on...

01:34.735 --> 01:35.861
Here you are,
Kevin Keegan.

01:35.936 --> 01:37.301
You get over here and take
this corner...

01:38.372 --> 01:39.100
Hurry up...

01:39.173 --> 01:40.231
What am I going to do?

01:40.307 --> 01:43.936
Roll them over and take them
back to the wagon...

01:44.011 --> 01:44.978
Come here...

01:45.045 --> 01:48.503
Keep in a straight line, make them
about a foot long...

01:48.582 --> 01:49.981
so you can roll them
up like a carpet...

01:50.050 --> 01:51.984
Here you are, dopey arse,
you get over here.

01:52.052 --> 01:54.179
Now go in sections
as fast as you can...

01:54.254 --> 01:56.188
a couple of barows and
we're up the road, all right!

02:04.331 --> 02:06.265
Now come, Dean, hurry up,
lad, will you!

02:13.440 --> 02:18.377
Too early for this sort of stuff
for me. I've got a bad back.

02:19.146 --> 02:22.707
Hey you, can't you keep up with
me here or what?

02:27.287 --> 02:28.777
Oh, keep them neat,
will you, lad...

02:28.855 --> 02:31.255
come on, Tommy
just make it safe there...

02:57.317 --> 02:57.942
Oi!

03:04.491 --> 03:06.391
Oh no!

03:06.460 --> 03:08.223
Communist bastards!

03:09.463 --> 03:11.488
We can pick up a roller from
a scrap-yard dirt cheap.

03:11.565 --> 03:14.056
All you want then is a roll
of twine, a couple of pegs...

03:14.134 --> 03:16.659
couple of banjoes, a plank,
a wheelbarrow and a rake.

03:16.737 --> 03:18.136
We're on our way.

03:18.205 --> 03:19.672
Yeah, to do the businesses
properly.

03:19.740 --> 03:21.605
Now, it all depends if I get
my hands on a van.

03:21.675 --> 03:23.336
Just put an advert
in the local paper.

03:23.410 --> 03:24.536
And I'll need me phone
putting in.

03:24.611 --> 03:26.408
Correct. As soon as a local
punter rings up...

03:26.480 --> 03:27.845
I go down,
measure the job...

03:27.914 --> 03:30.576
go nick the turf, lay it down,
get paid all in the same day.

03:30.651 --> 03:31.709
You ever done it before?

03:31.785 --> 03:34.481
Dead easy, lad, like laying carpet
tiles, isn't it?

03:34.554 --> 03:35.953
Just make sure the underneath's
dead flat.

03:36.023 --> 03:36.853
Where do we get
the turf from?

03:36.923 --> 03:38.220
Parks, gardens, cemeteries...

03:38.292 --> 03:39.850
And Conservative Clubs!

03:39.960 --> 03:41.484
Well that's the best
quality stuff.

03:41.561 --> 03:43.324
We get a few extra bob
for that, don't we?

03:43.397 --> 03:44.659
But I've got to get
a van.

03:44.731 --> 03:46.562
Where we going to
get a van from?

03:55.375 --> 03:59.402
To ensure tenancy arrangement
under the private landlords...

03:59.479 --> 04:01.470
So, where does the difference
come in?

04:01.548 --> 04:03.573
The difference is you've got
no you've got no protection...

04:17.397 --> 04:19.058
If you get any problems at all,
give us a shout.

04:19.132 --> 04:20.463
Yeah, okay.

04:20.534 --> 04:21.728
Hello, Bob.
/Hello, Jimmy.

04:21.802 --> 04:22.734
This is my son-in-law,
Bob.

04:22.803 --> 04:23.792
Pleased to meet you...

04:23.870 --> 04:25.895
This is Ken Rider, councillor.

04:25.972 --> 04:27.371
Second prize again, eh?

04:27.441 --> 04:29.136
I hope you got it
fighting for the working class.

04:29.209 --> 04:30.267
I've got to go now.

04:30.344 --> 04:31.368
Give us a ring.
/Nice one.

04:31.445 --> 04:32.309
No problem.

04:34.114 --> 04:34.773
All right, son.

04:34.848 --> 04:36.145
Listen...

04:36.216 --> 04:37.979
I'm after a van. You don't
know anyone, do you?

04:38.051 --> 04:39.211
A van?

04:39.286 --> 04:40.753
Yeah, nothing fancy.

04:40.821 --> 04:41.719
Have you got the money?

04:41.788 --> 04:42.720
Depends on the price.

04:42.789 --> 04:44.279
But without a van
I can't work.

04:44.358 --> 04:47.384
Er... hang on, I'm sure there's
a card come in yesterday.

04:47.461 --> 04:48.291
Cheers, Jimmy.

04:50.897 --> 04:52.091
Yeah... this is it.

04:52.165 --> 04:53.427
This is it.

04:55.969 --> 04:57.766
Only come in yesterday
this, Bob.

04:58.872 --> 05:01.363
Let's look at that.
Two-sixty!

05:01.441 --> 05:03.068
Well he won't rip you off,
you know...

05:03.143 --> 05:04.508
you know Cliff, don't you?

05:04.578 --> 05:07.604
Cliff... oh, is that the little guy
always wears a boiler suit full of grease?

05:07.681 --> 05:08.773
Lives on Hollins.

05:08.849 --> 05:10.476
I'll give that a look at,
cheers.

05:11.485 --> 05:13.146
You're looking a mess,
you know, son.

05:13.220 --> 05:14.778
I feel a mess.

05:14.855 --> 05:16.982
Listen, what did this Communion
dress cost you?

05:17.057 --> 05:18.285
Oh, has our Anne been talking?

05:18.358 --> 05:19.848
Anne hasn't mentioned
it, son.

05:19.926 --> 05:22.019
Young Coleen's been coming around
telling me all about it...

05:22.095 --> 05:23.153
and I put two and
two together...

05:23.230 --> 05:25.255
you know, it must have cost
you a bomb.

05:26.266 --> 05:27.893
Yeah, a good few
quid, yeah.

05:27.968 --> 05:29.162
But I'll manage.

05:29.236 --> 05:31.796
Aye, so I see. Look.
/No, you look!

05:31.872 --> 05:33.635
I've got a lot of respect
for you, Jimmy...

05:33.707 --> 05:35.140
but this is none
of your business.

05:35.208 --> 05:36.505
Bobby... we're family.

05:36.576 --> 05:38.942
Look, I got meself in this mess,
I'll get meself out.

05:39.012 --> 05:40.570
Not through the Church
you won't, son.

05:40.647 --> 05:42.012
What's the Church
got to do with it?

05:42.082 --> 05:43.743
Because you're looking for
answers and there isn't any...

05:43.817 --> 05:45.648
because they're part
of the problem.

05:45.719 --> 05:48.483
Look, you've got
your beliefs...

05:48.555 --> 05:50.648
I've got mine.
Okay?

05:50.724 --> 05:52.919
No, what you've got
is fear.

05:52.993 --> 05:55.791
And five Hail Marys ain't
going to help what ails you.

05:55.862 --> 05:57.591
Because all this religious
mumbo-jumbo...

05:57.664 --> 06:00.758
all it does is tire your mind
and stop you thinking for yourself.

06:00.834 --> 06:03.803
Look, Jimmy, the last thing I need
right now is a lecture.

06:03.870 --> 06:05.201
Or a sermon.

06:05.272 --> 06:07.137
No what you need is a job
and there aren't any.

06:07.207 --> 06:09.175
Oh, now tell us something
I don't know.

06:09.242 --> 06:13.303
When you're a worker, it
'rains stones' seven days a week.

06:13.380 --> 06:15.280
And then it pisses
down on me.

06:15.348 --> 06:16.679
Ah, not only on
you, Bob...

06:16.750 --> 06:19.116
you see, you're walking around
with this individual guilt...

06:19.186 --> 06:21.586
and this is what they want.
It's destroying you.

06:21.655 --> 06:24.055
God knows, you know, given
half the chance I know
you're a grafter.

06:24.124 --> 06:25.751
It's not done us much good,
though, has it?

06:25.826 --> 06:27.555
We never invented
the system, son...

06:27.627 --> 06:29.219
but it's up to us to change it.

06:29.296 --> 06:31.161
What's that?
/Slanging match.

06:38.405 --> 06:39.497
Smack-heads!

06:39.573 --> 06:41.507
But she can't be any more
than fifteen.

06:42.909 --> 06:43.603
You've got my ring!

06:43.677 --> 06:45.042
I haven't, Ellen! I haven't
got your ring!

06:45.111 --> 06:46.373
Well you've got me money then,
haven't you?

06:46.446 --> 06:47.378
No! Cos I want to score
tonight as well.

06:47.447 --> 06:49.210
You're a liar!
You're a liar!

06:49.282 --> 06:52.217
I need to score tonight.
You know for a fact...

06:52.285 --> 06:53.752
What chance have they got?

06:53.820 --> 06:55.845
You know, one or two might
slip through the net...

06:55.922 --> 06:57.947
but for the rest of them,
it's, you know, it's mapped out...

06:58.024 --> 06:59.491
it's all cut and dried.

06:59.559 --> 07:00.457
They've got no work...

07:00.527 --> 07:01.585
no hope...

07:01.661 --> 07:02.491
it's all despair.

07:02.562 --> 07:06.191
All the they've got is crime,
booze, drugs...

07:06.266 --> 07:08.166
families just breaking up.

07:08.235 --> 07:10.760
And do you know, it could be
a lovely estate to live on.

07:10.837 --> 07:13.670
Do you know, we're like punch
drunk fighters hammering
at each other...

07:13.740 --> 07:18.507
instead of us getting together and
sharing around the power for us
to make all the changes...

07:18.578 --> 07:21.604
and that's all it is in a nutshell,
the rest is propaganda.

07:25.719 --> 07:26.845
It'll do about thirty to the gallon
on the road.

07:26.920 --> 07:27.648
Let's have a look round here...

07:27.721 --> 07:29.086
Hang on, hang on a minute,
Tommy...

07:29.155 --> 07:30.952
Well, you have a look.
I'll have a look here.

07:31.024 --> 07:31.718
Yeah, but Tommy...

07:31.791 --> 07:34.692
Oh, come on Cliff, play the game,
look at the bloody bodywork, son.

07:34.761 --> 07:35.420
What's wrong with
that?

07:35.495 --> 07:38.362
Jesus Christ, there's more
filler here than on Barbara
Cartland's face!

07:38.431 --> 07:40.331
There's some spots of fillers...

07:40.400 --> 07:42.061
Look at that, the tyres are
bleedin' baldy.

07:42.135 --> 07:43.193
They're remoulds.

07:43.270 --> 07:43.827
Yeah?

07:43.904 --> 07:46.270
Yeah, well, you don't see
the tread with remoulds, do you.

07:46.339 --> 07:47.271
You're joking,
aren't you!

07:47.340 --> 07:49.171
I've seen more rubber on a
bleedin' French letter!

07:49.242 --> 07:50.732
You must have a big
French letter.

07:50.810 --> 07:52.243
You've got new tyres
on the front!

07:52.312 --> 07:54.371
Hey, Cliff... I'm having it.

07:54.447 --> 07:56.210
Right, how are you
having it, then?

07:56.283 --> 07:58.114
Is there any chance of us, er...
knocking the price down?

07:58.184 --> 07:59.344
Oh, here we go now,
knock it down!

07:59.419 --> 08:00.545
How many owners has
it had?

08:00.620 --> 08:01.882
Owners! Only one owner!

08:01.955 --> 08:03.479
Who was it, fucking Ben Hur?
/Who's Ben hur?

08:03.557 --> 08:04.285
Come on, Cliff!

08:04.357 --> 08:05.289
Does he live on the Estate?

08:05.358 --> 08:08.953
Cliff, Cliff...
I'm buying the thing, right?

08:09.029 --> 08:10.792
Can we knock it down to
two hundred?

08:12.699 --> 08:14.997
How can you do that,
I've got to make some money...

08:15.068 --> 08:18.936
He's lost his mother! I'm going to
lose my wife if I sell it for any
less than that.

08:19.005 --> 08:19.835
Two hundred?

08:19.906 --> 08:22.568
No, two sixty, and
that's it.

08:22.642 --> 08:24.234
Cliff, I haven't got that
amount of money on me.

08:24.311 --> 08:26.506
What about if we can come
to some sort of deal?

08:27.647 --> 08:30.207
Can I pay you weekly...

08:30.283 --> 08:33.878
So you're paying half the price of
the two sixty, right?

08:33.953 --> 08:36.923
And a tenner a week.

08:36.990 --> 08:39.549
Can you manage that? I don't
want any pissing about.

08:39.626 --> 08:41.594
If you say a tenner
a week, I want it.

09:07.487 --> 09:09.887
Mum! Dad's got
a new van!

09:11.157 --> 09:12.715
I'm going downstairs
and see him.

09:28.041 --> 09:29.804
Hey, dad!
/Coleen...

09:31.211 --> 09:32.508
Yeah, look at this!

09:32.579 --> 09:34.376
What! Is is this ours!
/Like it?

09:34.447 --> 09:36.074
Yeah, it's great,
isn't it?

09:36.149 --> 09:37.514
Come on, let me show you
the inside.

09:39.152 --> 09:41.347
What do you think?

09:42.355 --> 09:45.324
That's ours?
/Yeah, it's not bad, is it?

09:45.392 --> 09:47.292
Why didn't you tell me
you were getting a van?

09:47.360 --> 09:49.988
It came out of the blue. A bargain,
two sixty. Snatched his hand off.

09:50.063 --> 09:51.758
Two sixty?

09:51.831 --> 09:53.799
Look, the bloke I'm getting
it off is a mate of mine.

09:53.867 --> 09:57.462
And he says I can pay him back
bit-by-bit once I start earning
the money.

09:57.537 --> 10:00.165
Ah, come on, this is us, kid,
we're on our way up now.

10:00.740 --> 10:01.832
I can start earning
wages with this.

10:01.908 --> 10:04.274
In fact, I've already pulled one
little job on the way down.

10:04.344 --> 10:06.244
Yeah?
/Moving a little bit of furniture...

10:06.312 --> 10:07.609
so it's a start.

10:07.681 --> 10:09.273
Oh, it's got to be
right, this.

10:09.349 --> 10:11.044
It's going to make it for us.
So what do you reckon?

10:12.352 --> 10:14.320
Well, it could do with a bit
of a clean, couldn't it?

10:14.387 --> 10:15.979
Bit of elbow grease and
it'll be fine, this.

10:16.056 --> 10:18.684
Dad, when can we have
a ride in it?

10:18.758 --> 10:20.191
Later love, later.
But for now...

10:20.260 --> 10:22.854
you can sit in the driver's seat and
play with the steering wheel.

10:22.962 --> 10:25.487
There you go. Get in there.
Have a go on the steering wheel.

10:26.132 --> 10:28.464
Hey, can earn some money
with this, love.

10:28.535 --> 10:30.025
Brilliant!

10:38.878 --> 10:39.537
Ta-ta, love...

10:42.982 --> 10:43.744
Hello, Gilbert.

10:43.817 --> 10:44.977
Hello, Bob.
Are you all right?

10:45.051 --> 10:46.541
Yeah, fine.
Better now.

10:46.619 --> 10:48.644
I know what you mean,
mate, yeah.

10:48.722 --> 10:50.713
Yeah, see you later
then, Bob.

10:58.364 --> 11:00.093
You little shithead!
/I was going to pay you!

11:00.166 --> 11:01.326
Oh, yeah! Were you?

11:01.401 --> 11:03.266
I've got the money! I was going
to pay you!

11:05.705 --> 11:06.899
I've got the money!

11:06.973 --> 11:07.735
I want it now!

11:07.807 --> 11:08.933
I've got it!

11:13.780 --> 11:15.042
You never give me
a chance.

11:15.115 --> 11:16.946
When you borrow money,
you pay it back.

11:17.016 --> 11:18.415
Right.
/Right!

11:18.485 --> 11:20.817
And never mind spending it
at bookies.

11:20.887 --> 11:22.013
Look, we want this
every week...

11:22.088 --> 11:23.385
Right...
/Every week.

11:23.456 --> 11:24.548
You owe a lot of money!
/Right! Right!

11:24.624 --> 11:25.989
Don't spend it
in the bookies...

11:26.059 --> 11:27.026
I'm warning you!
/I won't!

11:27.093 --> 11:28.253
A warning!
/Okay...

11:30.396 --> 11:32.626
Oh, yes...
part time cleaners...

11:32.699 --> 11:34.223
evening shifts
for city centre.

11:34.300 --> 11:37.167
Mmm... that looks all right,
doesn't it, where is it?

11:37.237 --> 11:38.397
Oh, Stretford.

11:38.471 --> 11:40.268
Waste of time,
isn't it, that?

11:40.340 --> 11:42.672
Travel'd be a week's wages,
wouldn't it?

11:42.742 --> 11:44.369
See if there's anything else.

11:45.311 --> 11:46.539
"Returning to work..."

11:46.613 --> 11:47.409
Mum?

11:47.480 --> 11:47.946
Yeah?

11:48.014 --> 11:49.538
Can I have some money to go
to the chippy, please?

11:49.616 --> 11:51.413
Oh, he's always after money,
our Sean. Come here.

11:51.484 --> 11:52.815
Ta.

11:53.953 --> 11:56.183
Um...

11:56.256 --> 11:57.655
Right, I want some change.

11:57.724 --> 11:58.452
Okay...

11:58.525 --> 12:00.857
I shouldn't be too long, right.
I'll be home in a bit.

12:00.927 --> 12:02.792
Mum... can I play out...
/Come straight home, bye.

12:02.862 --> 12:04.523
Yeah, of course you can.
Put your coat on.

12:06.666 --> 12:10.033
"...earn pounds at home.
Experienced machinists required...

12:10.103 --> 12:12.037
for making baby buggy hoods
and aprons."

12:12.105 --> 12:13.868
Aye, I wonder how much
that is?

12:13.940 --> 12:15.305
It's usually cash
in hand.

12:15.375 --> 12:17.673
I used to get 12p
an apron...

12:17.744 --> 12:21.680
and if I really was good,
you know, disciplined myself
and put the hours in...

12:21.748 --> 12:23.773
I'd get between ten and twelve
quid a day.

12:23.850 --> 12:25.374
Sounds like it'd do us,
that.

12:25.451 --> 12:27.112
You've got to be fast.

12:27.187 --> 12:28.654
I've not sewed
in ages.

12:28.721 --> 12:31.246
Soon get back into the swing
of things, don't you.

12:31.324 --> 12:32.450
Eh, mum...
/Yeah... yeah?

12:34.794 --> 12:36.955
An ambulance has just pulled up
outside Mrs Whittaker's house

12:37.564 --> 12:38.792
and the people in the chippy said
that she's took an overdose...

12:38.898 --> 12:39.796
Let's have a look.

12:50.677 --> 12:52.406
You know, it doesn't
surprise me, this.

12:52.478 --> 12:54.309
She got caught for doing
the meter.

12:54.380 --> 12:56.371
Did she?
/Yeah, about three weeks ago.

12:57.383 --> 12:58.975
You know, it gets you like that,
dunnit?

12:59.052 --> 13:00.883
Yeah, but throwing the towel
in's not the answer, is it?

13:00.954 --> 13:02.979
She's got three kids,
for Christ's sake.

13:03.590 --> 13:07.424
Mmm... it's funny how we start off,
innit, with all these big ideas...

13:07.493 --> 13:10.690
and you realise that things aren't
going to change...

13:10.763 --> 13:12.424
Well... no...

13:12.498 --> 13:14.295
Like Bob's prospects.

13:14.367 --> 13:15.664
When's he going to
get a job?

13:15.735 --> 13:18.727
Well, Tommy's like that, he's been
trying for ages, he's give up now.

13:20.173 --> 13:21.333
Do you know...

13:21.407 --> 13:24.069
I'll live and die in that flat and
nobody'll even know.

13:24.711 --> 13:26.736
But at least you're not on your
own, are you?

13:28.514 --> 13:30.880
I reckon we should
go out one night...

13:30.950 --> 13:33.248
and get ourselves a couple
of sugar daddies.

13:33.319 --> 13:33.910
Do you reckon?
/Yeah...

13:40.193 --> 13:42.388
