33:07.859 --> 33:08.826
What do you mean?

33:09.728 --> 33:10.387
Come in.

33:23.975 --> 33:27.604
What is it, Bob?
What's happening...

33:29.548 --> 33:31.072
Sit yourself down.

33:38.457 --> 33:39.253
What's up?

33:39.891 --> 33:41.324
I'm in terrible trouble,
Father.

33:42.360 --> 33:43.520
What kind of trouble?

33:43.595 --> 33:45.722
I've been responsible
for a man's death.

33:47.032 --> 33:49.330
You... you killed someone?

33:49.401 --> 33:51.631
No, it was an accident.
An accident.

33:51.703 --> 33:53.000
I didn't mean to.

33:53.872 --> 33:55.499
To a man named Tansey.

33:56.241 --> 33:58.937
The loan shark?
/Yeah...

34:00.812 --> 34:02.973
You fought with him?
/Yeah...

34:04.883 --> 34:08.444
About what?
/Money.

34:09.987 --> 34:11.216
You borrowed from him?

34:12.056 --> 34:14.525
No. I borrowed
from a loan company...

34:15.127 --> 34:16.594
...but I couldn't keep
the payments up...

34:17.161 --> 34:18.789
...and Tansey got hold of
the debts.

34:19.431 --> 34:22.092
That's what he does.
Debts and drugs.

34:22.167 --> 34:23.862
So I heard.

34:23.935 --> 34:27.199
How much?
/A hundred and fifty pound.

34:27.772 --> 34:32.572
To pay for Coleen's dress?
/Yes, it was the only way.

34:32.643 --> 34:35.737
Bob... I thought
you had more sense.

34:37.815 --> 34:39.511
Hold your horses
there for a second.

35:15.086 --> 35:16.553
I took these out of
his pocket.

35:18.256 --> 35:18.950
What is it?

35:19.925 --> 35:21.688
It's the book
with all the names in.

35:21.760 --> 35:23.125
That's the money
they all owe.

35:24.229 --> 35:27.255
And if... if they don't pay he
goes round and breaks their legs.

35:27.332 --> 35:28.890
That's why the call him
the Collector.

35:30.302 --> 35:32.497
I boil up inside,
sometimes I get angry.

35:33.104 --> 35:34.401
But I'm a grafter.

35:34.472 --> 35:35.666
I know that.

35:35.740 --> 35:39.642
I get up every morning and go
looking for work, wherever it is...

35:40.845 --> 35:42.312
I'm a good Catholic,
Father.

35:43.014 --> 35:45.278
I go to church, I believe in
God, I pray...

35:45.350 --> 35:48.046
but it doesn't put food
on the table.

35:50.322 --> 35:51.448
When did this happen?

35:51.523 --> 35:53.115
About an hour ago.

35:53.191 --> 35:54.783
So he's still lying
in the car?

35:54.859 --> 35:56.190
As far as I know, yeah.

35:56.261 --> 35:57.592
Does anyone else
know about it?

35:57.662 --> 35:58.356
No.

35:58.430 --> 36:00.295
Just us?
/Yeah...

36:02.300 --> 36:03.927
What are you going to do
about it, Bob?

36:04.469 --> 36:07.165
I'm going to have to go
the police, what else can I do?

36:07.239 --> 36:11.198
But I don't... I don't want them
going round telling Anne
and Coleen...

36:11.276 --> 36:13.267
...I want you to do that, Father,
please.

36:13.345 --> 36:15.836
I want you to do it
because I can't.

36:17.015 --> 36:19.779
I can't...
/Why should you?

36:19.851 --> 36:20.909
What?

36:20.986 --> 36:22.681
Tell Anne.

36:23.355 --> 36:24.379
Tansey's dead.

36:24.456 --> 36:25.684
Fuck Tansey!

36:26.625 --> 36:29.458
May God have mercy on his soul.
You didn't kill him.

36:29.527 --> 36:31.119
No. It was an accident.

36:31.196 --> 36:32.857
Yes, it was an accident.

36:32.931 --> 36:36.332
So why sacrifice your freedom
and the happiness of your family?

36:37.669 --> 36:40.137
There's lots of good people
on this Estate...

36:40.205 --> 36:43.368
...will sleep easier in their beds
because of his passing.

36:43.441 --> 36:46.035
They were afraid of him, Father.
They were afraid of him.

36:48.313 --> 36:50.907
You came to me
for advice and help.

36:51.883 --> 36:53.748
Then stay away from
the police.

36:53.818 --> 36:56.582
Go home and pray for Tansey's
worthless soul.

36:57.188 --> 36:59.554
Say nothing to Anne
or to anyone.

37:01.359 --> 37:03.190
First thing we do is get rid
of this lot.

37:21.246 --> 37:23.009
You're not an evil
man, Bob.

37:23.748 --> 37:26.444
People like yourself are
hungering for justice...

37:26.518 --> 37:30.113
in the name of Christ who was
himself the bread of life...

37:30.188 --> 37:31.485
you deserve it.

37:32.624 --> 37:34.148
Now I'll hear
your confession.

37:46.738 --> 37:49.673
In the name of the Father and
the Son and of the Holy Spirit,
amen.

37:52.344 --> 37:53.276
Forgive me Father...

37:54.279 --> 37:55.211
for I have sinned.

37:56.381 --> 37:57.609
Over in that corner
there...
/Coleen?

37:57.682 --> 37:59.809
Hey, lads...
/Coleen!

37:59.884 --> 38:02.011
Do you mind standing over
in that corner there, please.

38:02.087 --> 38:04.521
Just over here.
Come on, lads.

38:09.694 --> 38:11.491
Everyone line up just there.
That's the idea.

38:11.563 --> 38:12.894
Just over there a little
bit, son.

38:14.132 --> 38:16.760
Now, just come a bit closer in.
That's it, and lift baby up.

38:16.835 --> 38:18.063
Just behave yourself.

38:18.603 --> 38:22.198
I know you don't want to be
here but just behave yourself.

38:22.273 --> 38:23.103
Right.

38:28.346 --> 38:29.472
What, you got
problems, mate?

38:29.547 --> 38:30.411
Just a minute...

38:31.449 --> 38:32.575
Did you hear about
Tansey?

38:32.650 --> 38:35.346
I believe he became unstuck
in a car crash.

38:35.420 --> 38:37.183
Unstuck! He's as dead
as a bloody dodo!

38:37.255 --> 38:38.051
How did it happen?

38:38.123 --> 38:40.057
Just run into a concrete wall
or something.

38:40.125 --> 38:40.955
Pissed?

38:41.025 --> 38:42.492
Stoned out of his head,
I believe.

38:42.560 --> 38:44.357
Couldn't have happened
to a nicer fella.

38:44.429 --> 38:45.896
Mr Williams can I have your
attention, please.

38:45.964 --> 38:47.022
...just face the camera.

38:47.098 --> 38:48.065
Now everybody a big
smile...

38:48.133 --> 38:49.327
I've seen more life
in a sick note!

38:49.401 --> 38:50.333
Come on, everybody!

38:51.069 --> 38:56.029
One, two... Mr. Williams...
Mr. Williams!

38:56.608 --> 38:57.632
Bob, stop it!

38:57.709 --> 38:58.676
Mr. Williams...

38:58.743 --> 39:00.370
...now face the camera,
that's the idea...

39:00.445 --> 39:01.434
...after three, a big smile...

39:01.513 --> 39:04.710
one... two...
three... cheese!

39:04.783 --> 39:05.909
Mr. Williams?

39:25.270 --> 39:27.101
The day before
He suffered...

39:27.172 --> 39:29.606
He took bread
in his sacred hands...

39:29.674 --> 39:32.802
and looking up to Heaven, to you,
His Almighty Father...

39:32.877 --> 39:34.902
He gave you
thanks and praise.

39:34.979 --> 39:38.779
He broke the bread, gave it
to his disciples and said...

39:39.417 --> 39:42.284
"Take this all of
you and eat it...

39:42.353 --> 39:45.811
this is my body which will be
given up for you."

39:55.133 --> 39:57.465
When supper was ended
He took the cup...

39:57.535 --> 39:59.730
again He gave you thanks
and praise...

39:59.804 --> 40:02.466
gave the cup to His disciples
and said...

40:02.540 --> 40:05.771
"take this all of you and
drink from it...

40:05.844 --> 40:07.869
this is the cup
of my blood...

40:07.946 --> 40:10.574
the blood of the new and
everlasting covenant...

40:10.648 --> 40:13.242
it will be shed for you
and for all men...

40:13.318 --> 40:15.252
so that sins maybe forgiven."

40:25.163 --> 40:25.891
Yes?

40:25.964 --> 40:26.623
Hello, love.

40:26.698 --> 40:28.689
Does, er, Mr. Robert Williams
live here?

40:28.766 --> 40:30.461
Yeah. But he's not
here.

40:30.535 --> 40:32.127
Can you tell me when
he may be back?

40:32.203 --> 40:34.501
Well, I don't know. He's gone
to church. Why?

40:34.572 --> 40:36.540
Does he own a green
Transit van...

40:36.608 --> 40:38.303
...BRJ 563Y?

40:38.376 --> 40:39.934
Yeah, but it's been stolen.

40:40.011 --> 40:42.741
Well, we've found it.
It's in the police pound
at Collyhurst.

40:42.814 --> 40:45.510
I wonder if you'd give him
a message, ask him to collect it.

41:16.648 --> 41:17.808
The body of Christ...

41:18.516 --> 41:19.505
Amen...

